l island off the western edge of the UK produces one of the most exported beers of all time with Guinness Irish Dry Stout. 1759 was …<p> <a class="continue-reading-link" href="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/2015/12/the-brewery-that-conquered-the-world/">Continue reading<i class="icon-right-dir"></i></a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"nkosio";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17979:"<div id="attachment_10744" style="width: 910px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/2015/12/the-brewery-that-conquered-the-world/guinness-entrance/" rel="attachment wp-att-10744"><img class="size-large wp-image-10744" src="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/guinness-entrance-1024x486.jpg" alt="St. James's Gate, Dublin, Ireland." width="900" height="427" srcset="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/guinness-entrance-300x142.jpg 300w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/guinness-entrance-768x364.jpg 768w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/guinness-entrance-1024x486.jpg 1024w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/guinness-entrance-250x119.jpg 250w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/guinness-entrance-150x71.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">St. James&#8217;s Gate, Dublin, Ireland.</p></div>
<p>You could argue that this is the most iconic brewery on the planet. Over 10 million pints sold daily in 150 countries. Ireland, this small island off the western edge of the UK produces one of the most exported beers of all time with Guinness Irish Dry Stout.</p>
<p>1759 was the year things got started for Sir Arthur Guinness’ brewery. The original location sat on 4 acres; the current space at St James&#8217;s Gate occupies over 50 acres. The Storehouse is the seven-story visitors center on the brewery complex grounds that is parts history museum, taproom, art gallery, restaurant, and event space. Aside from the Chicago style architecture, the most impressive attribute of the Storehouse would be the employees that live and breathe the company’s accomplishments.</p>
<p>The space literally holds five miles of archive papers. Very few moments in my beer travels were cooler than waking up in Dublin and taking a cab to Guinness with 13 beer writers to experience a collection that includes a brewery notebook from October 24<sup>th</sup> 1801.</p>
