<p>Nights like this are what make Chicago so special. An all-star lineup up chefs and mixologists gathered for a friendly Sunday afternoon competition / showcase in West Loop at the 7th Annual Cochon 555 Heritage BBQ. Cochon’s mission is to support farmers by educating the public through events about heritage breed pigs.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div id="attachment_10409" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image41.jpg"><img class="wp-image-10409" src="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image41-1024x680.jpg" alt="my favorite dish may have been this chix/ pork dumpling" width="600" height="398" srcset="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image41-300x199.jpg 300w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image41-1024x680.jpg 1024w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image41-226x150.jpg 226w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">My favorite dish may have been this chicken/ pork dumpling</p></div>
<div id="attachment_10416" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Screen-Shot-2015-10-09-at-1.11.16-PM.png"><img class="wp-image-10416" src="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Screen-Shot-2015-10-09-at-1.11.16-PM-1024x557.png" alt="The Butcher &amp; Larder's popup butcher shop" width="600" height="326" srcset="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Screen-Shot-2015-10-09-at-1.11.16-PM-300x163.png 300w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Screen-Shot-2015-10-09-at-1.11.16-PM-1024x557.png 1024w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Screen-Shot-2015-10-09-at-1.11.16-PM-250x136.png 250w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Screen-Shot-2015-10-09-at-1.11.16-PM.png 1094w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">The Butcher &amp; Larder&#8217;s popup butcher shop</p></div>
<p>Morgan Manufacturing in West Loop was the perfect location for this end-of-summer romp. It’s a completely renovated event space that existed pre-Great Chicago Fire. The building is the one of the best examples of modern industrial elegance that you will find on the events circuit. I love partying here; it’s somehow both contemporary and old-fashioned all at once. We enjoyed a weeknight prohibition era scotch event with Cutty Sark in the venue last winter.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Five of the 12 chefs in attendance competed in the culinary challenge. Each cooked one whole pig from a family farm. The winner would we be crowned King/Queen BBQ and take home $3,000 in prizes.</p>
<div id="attachment_10411" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image2.png"><img class="wp-image-10411" src="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image2.png" alt="The Perfect Manhattan" width="600" height="479" srcset="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image2-300x239.png 300w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image2-188x150.png 188w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image2-150x120.png 150w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image2.png 652w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">The Perfect Manhattan</p></div>
<div id="attachment_10412" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image1.png"><img class="wp-image-10412" src="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image1.png" alt="Smoked Manhattans featuring bourbon from the 2013 distillery of the year - Breckenridge " width="600" height="514" srcset="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image1-300x257.png 300w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image1-175x150.png 175w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image1.png 340w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Smoked Manhattans featuring bourbon from the 2013 distillery of the year &#8211; Breckenridge</p></div>
<p>Between enjoying chefs creations we crossed paths with a pair of fun beverages that combined our two favorite things &#8211; beer and whiskey.</p>
<p>George Dickel Tennessee Whiskey had quite the buzz going with their Peach Bit cocktail. Peach infused whiskey, honey syrup and <a href="http://moodytongue.com/"><strong>Moody Tongue</strong></a> Sliced Nectarine IPA over ice. You can learn all about their unique style of whiskey <a href="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/2014/12/the-tennessee-sippin-whisky-dinner/"><strong>here</strong></a>.</p>
<p>The lone beer on the menu was the Carhartt Woodsman by<a href="http://newhollandbrew.com/"><strong> New Holland Brewing</strong></a>. It’s a barrel aged pale ale collaboration with Carhartt. The legendary work gear brand celebrated their 125<sup>th</sup> anniversary last year. Both of these Michigan-based companies joined forced to commemorate the occasion.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Unlike most brewers, New Holland is also a distillery with 15 different spirit offerings in their portfolio. Lets talk about Beer Barrel Bourbon for a second. It starts in new American oak barrels, but it’s finished in second-use barrels that previously aged Dragon’s Milk.</p>
<p>The flagship ale for New Holland is Dragon’s Milk, first brewed in 2001. Allowing a whiskey to age in oak beer barrels that previously held a Russian Imperial Stout creates a ridiculously soft yet robust profile.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div id="attachment_10413" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image11.jpg"><img class="wp-image-10413" src="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image11-1024x680.jpg" alt="George Dickel Tennessee Sipping Whiskey" width="600" height="398" srcset="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image11-300x199.jpg 300w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image11-1024x680.jpg 1024w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image11-226x150.jpg 226w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image11.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">George Dickel Tennessee Sipping Whiskey</p></div>
<div id="attachment_10414" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image21.png"><img class="wp-image-10414" src="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image21-1024x646.png" alt="I mean who doesnt love tiki" width="600" height="378" srcset="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image21-300x189.png 300w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image21-1024x646.png 1024w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image21-238x150.png 238w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image21.png 1034w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">I mean who doesn&#8217;t love tiki</p></div>
<div id="attachment_10415" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image33.jpg"><img class="wp-image-10415" src="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image33-1024x768.jpg" alt="brewery/ distillery, New Holland, Michigan" width="600" height="450" srcset="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image33-300x225.jpg 300w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image33-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image33-200x150.jpg 200w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/image33.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Brewery/ Distillery, New Holland, Michigan</p></div>
<p>For seven years Cochon has spotlighted chefs in a way that celebrates global grilling cultures. This year <a href="http://www.analoguechicago.com/"><strong>Analogue Chicago</strong></a> chef Alfredo Nogueira took home top honors as King BBQ. Alfredo is a New Orleans’s native that moved to Chicago after Hurricane Katrina. He started making gumbo for friends as a way to cure being homesick.</p>
<p>The night ended with a threesome of magical offerings that appeared from the kitchen via the good folks at<a href="http://www.bangbangpie.com/"><strong> Bang Bang Pie Shop</strong></a>. The dessert cart included bacon bourbon pecan pie, key lime and a peach cobbler for the win.</p>
<div id="attachment_10417" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Screen-Shot-2015-10-09-at-1.17.45-PM.png"><img class="wp-image-10417" src="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Screen-Shot-2015-10-09-at-1.17.45-PM.png" alt="The Bang Bang Pies dessert cart literally fell from heaven" width="600" height="320" srcset="http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Screen-Shot-2015-10-09-at-1.17.45-PM-300x160.png 300w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Screen-Shot-2015-10-09-at-1.17.45-PM-250x133.png 250w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Screen-Shot-2015-10-09-at-1.17.45-PM-150x80.png 150w, http://www.chicagobeergeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Screen-Shot-2015-10-09-at-1.17.45-PM.png 976w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">The Bang Bang Pies dessert cart literally fell from heaven</p></div>
